The Patron of the Kaduna Chamber of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture (KADCCIMA), Malam Abidu Yazid has described the chamber as a hub of international trade fair. Speaking yesterday at the investiture of the newly elected executives of the chamber, the patron assured that the chamber which serves the 36 states of the federation will stand firm to support all businesses to grow. “We serve as the hub of international trade fair and we serve the 36 states of the federation so for that reason, we need to give them assurances that we are standing firm to support them and their business and when they come to Kaduna for the trade fair.” He charged the new exco on playing key roles. “You are here to serve the business community of Kaduna and the rest of the country, please let us serve them and the best way we can serve them is to work together as one entity.” The immediate past president of the chamber and Executive Chairman of the Federal Character Commission (FCC) Dr Muheeeba Dankaka congratulated the new exco on their inauguration. She urged them to work together to ensure the success of the Kaduna International Trade Fair and beyond. On his part, the new president, Alhaji Suleiman Aliyu assured that he will build on the mandate given to him with the cooperation of all members to ensure that businesses are successful.